/auth/register sending response 
sendingResponse: {
The "Passthrough" Secret
Normally, if you use @Res(), NestJS stops handling the response and waits for you to manually call response.send(). By adding { passthrough: true },
you are telling NestJS:

"I want to touch the raw response (to set a cookie), but I still want you to handle sending the final JSON back to the frontend."
}